/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/uwerx_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Pool-directed_transferFrom_can_burn_more/codex_stderr_attempt2.log:1800:/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/uwerx_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Pool-directed_transferFrom_can_burn_more/codex_stderr_attempt0.log:1484:/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/uwerx_p5_25_124/rounds/round_1/merge_prompt.md:88:    "claim": "`uniswapPoolAddress` is fully mutable by the owner and gates the non-standard burn path. The owner can therefore redirect the extra-burn / exact-amount-revert behavior from the original pool to any arbitrary address with a single transaction.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/uwerx_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Pool-directed_transferFrom_can_burn_more/codex_stderr_attempt2.log:1801:/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/uwerx_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Pool-directed_transferFrom_can_burn_more/codex_stderr_attempt0.log:1485:/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/uwerx_p5_25_124/rounds/round_1/merge_prompt.md:111:[{"id": "F-001", "severity": "High", "confidence": "high", "title": "Owner can arbitrarily set pool address enabling fund theft", "locations": ["0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:282-284"], "claim": "The setUniswapPoolAddress function allows the owner to set any address as the Uniswap pool, which controls where the 3% sell tax (2% marketing + 1% burn) is applied.", "impact": "Owner can set the pool address to a malicious contract with callback hooks that can re-enter the transfer function or manipulate state to steal user funds. Additionally, owner can redirect the tax mechanism to collect fees or disable it entirely at will.", "paths": ["1. Owner calls setUniswapPoolAddress() to set pool to a malicious contract\n2. User transfers tokens to pool (selling)\n3. Malicious contract executes callback during transfer\n4. Attacker extracts additional value from user"]}, {"id": "F-002", "severity": "High", "confidence": "high", "title": "Owner can arbitrarily redirect marketing fee to any address", "locations": ["0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:286-288"], "claim": "The setMarketingWallet function allows the owner to change the marketing wallet address that receives 2% of each sell transaction.", "impact": "Owner can redirect the 2% marketing fee to any address, allowing collection of fees that should go to a designated marketing address. This creates a direct fund theft vector where owner can collect the fee portion of user transfers.", "paths": ["1. Owner calls setMarketingWallet() to set wallet to their own address\n2. User transfers tokens to pool (selling)\n3. 2% marketing fee is sent to owner's address instead of intended wallet"]}, {"id": "F-003", "severity": "Medium", "confidence": "high", "title": "No timelock on critical administrative functions", "locations": ["0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:282-288"], "claim": "setUniswapPoolAddress and setMarketingWallet execute immediately with no delay mechanism.", "impact": "Changes to critical protocol parameters (pool address, marketing wallet) take effect instantly. This allows owner to front-run large transfers or react instantly to market conditions, extracting maximum value before reverting changes. Users have no time to react to malicious parameter changes.", "paths": ["1. Owner monitors mempool for large pending transfer\n2. Owner front-runs by changing pool/marketing address\n3. Large transfer executes with modified parameters\n4. Owner reverts changes after extracting value"]}, {"id": "F-004", "severity": "Low", "confidence": "medium", "title": "Missing events for critical parameter changes", "locations": ["0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:282-288"], "claim": "setUniswapPoolAddress and setMarketingWallet do not emit events when changing state.", "impact": "No on-chain record of pool address or marketing wallet changes makes it difficult to track historical changes off-chain via event logs. This reduces transparency and makes it harder to detect suspicious changes.", "paths": []}, {"id": "F-005", "severity": "Informational", "confidence": "high", "title": "High owner concentration - single point of failure", "locations": ["0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:282-288"], "claim": "The owner has unrestricted control over critical token parameters including tax mechanism and fee collection.", "impact": "Single compromised owner key or malicious owner can completely control the token's economic parameters. No governance, multi-sig, or timelock protections exist. This is a centralization risk typical of pre-launch tokens but creates significant trust assumptions.", "paths": []}]
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/uwerx_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Pool-directed_transferFrom_can_burn_more/codex_stderr_attempt2.log:1802:/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/uwerx_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Pool-directed_transferFrom_can_burn_more/codex_stderr_attempt0.log:1505:/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/uwerx_p5_25_124/rounds/round_1/global_summary_stdout.log:4:- `0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol`: dominant focus across rounds; sell-path logic around `uniswapPoolAddress` and admin-settable addresses drive most risk
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/uwerx_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Pool-directed_transferFrom_can_burn_more/codex_stderr_attempt2.log:1803:/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/uwerx_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Pool-directed_transferFrom_can_burn_more/codex_stderr_attempt0.log:1506:/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/uwerx_p5_25_124/rounds/round_1/global_summary_stdout.log:11:- Special handling when `to == uniswapPoolAddress` creates a recurring direction around broken transfer accounting on sells
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/uwerx_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Pool-directed_transferFrom_can_burn_more/codex_stderr_attempt2.log:1804:/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/uwerx_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Pool-directed_transferFrom_can_burn_more/codex_stderr_attempt0.log:1507:/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/uwerx_p5_25_124/rounds/round_1/merge_stdout.log:1:{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Pool-directed transferFrom can burn more tokens than the approved allowance","locations":["0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:403","0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:409","0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:489","0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:496","0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:540"],"claim":"When `transferFrom(from, uniswapPoolAddress, amount)` is used, the contract spends allowance only for `amount`, then `_transfer` burns an additional `burnAmount` from `from` via `_burn(from, burnAmount)`. Because that extra burn is not covered by `_spendAllowance`, an approved spender can reduce the holder's balance by more than the approved amount.","impact":"Any spender or router approved for N tokens can cause the holder to lose N plus the extra burn on each pool-directed transfer. This violates expected ERC20 allowance boundaries and can create unauthorized user loss in integrations that rely on approvals as hard spend caps.","paths":["A holder approves a spender or router for `N` tokens.","The spender calls `transferFrom(holder, uniswapPoolAddress, N)`.","`_spendAllowance` deducts only `N`, but `_transfer` then calls `_burn(holder, burnAmount)`, removing additional balance without additional allowance."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Pool-directed transfers charge the burn on top of `amount`, causing exact-balance sells and exact-amount integrations to revert","locations":["0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:481","0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:484","0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:489","0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:496","0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:545"],"claim":"On transfers to `uniswapPoolAddress`, `_transfer` first removes the full `amount` from the sender and credits the recipient with that full `amount`, then separately calls `_burn(from, burnAmount)`. The sender therefore needs enough balance for `amount + burnAmount`, not just `amount`.","impact":"Users cannot exit with their full displayed balance to the configured pool, and protocols that attempt exact-amount sells, repayments, liquidations, or withdrawals to that address can revert unexpectedly. This can strand dust permanently and break integrations that assume `amount` is the total debited from the sender.","paths":["A user with balance `B` calls `transfer(uniswapPoolAddress, B)` or an integration tries to transfer an exact balance to the pool.","The contract subtracts `B` and credits the pool `B`, leaving the sender with zero.","`_burn(sender, burnAmount)` then reverts with `ERC20: burn amount exceeds balance` because the burn is charged on top of `amount`."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"Sell-path Transfer events do not match actual balance changes","locations":["0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:484","0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:487","0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:494","0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:495","0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:553"],"claim":"For transfers to `uniswapPoolAddress`, storage credits the pool with the full `amount` and never credits `marketingWalletAddress`, yet the contract emits events claiming only 97% reached the pool and 2% was sent to the marketing wallet. The event stream therefore misrepresents the actual token movements.","impact":"Indexers, accounting systems, tax tooling, snapshot systems, and exchange processors that rely on `Transfer` logs can record nonexistent marketing transfers and incorrect recipient amounts, causing reconciliation failures and potentially incorrect credits or balances off-chain.","paths":["A transfer is made to `uniswapPoolAddress`.","State changes give the pool the full `amount` and burn only the extra `burnAmount` from the sender.","The emitted logs instead describe a 97% transfer to the pool and a 2% transfer to `marketingWalletAddress`, which never occurred in storage."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Owner can retarget the broken sell-path logic to any arbitrary destination address","locations":["0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:282","0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:283","0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:489","0x4306b12f8e824ce1fa9604bbd88f2ad4f0fe3c54/Contract.sol:496"],"claim":"`uniswapPoolAddress` is owner-controlled and is the sole switch for the non-standard transfer path that over-burns senders, breaks exact-balance exits, and emits misleading logs. The owner can therefore redirect this punitive logic from the intended pool to any arbitrary address at any time.","impact":"A privileged owner can unexpectedly make transfers to a bridge, vault, exchange deposit address, router, or replacement pool start reverting exact-amount flows or charging extra sender loss. This creates a realistic griefing and integration-breakage vector for any protocol or user that sends tokens to the retargeted address.","paths":["The owner calls `setUniswapPoolAddress(target)`.","Users or protocols continue sending tokens to `target` under normal ERC20 assumptions.","Transfers to `target` now execute the broken sell-path logic, causing extra burns, exact-amount failures, and misleading logs for that destination."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Owner can arbitrarily set pool address enabling fund theft","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The code does let the owner retarget the special transfer path, but it does not call external contracts during transfer, so the claimed malicious callback/reentrancy theft path is unsupported. This is better framed as owner-retargetable griefing/integration breakage, which is captured in F-004."},{"title":"Owner can arbitrarily redirect marketing fee to any address","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`marketingWalletAddress` is never credited in storage. On sell-path transfers the contract only emits a synthetic `Transfer` event to that address, so changing it does not redirect actual token balances or create a real fee-theft vector."},{"title":"No timelock on critical administrative functions","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Lack of a timelock is a governance/centralization concern, not a standalone vulnerability here. The reportable issue is the underlying owner-retargetable broken transfer logic, not the absence of a delay mechanism."},{"title":"Missing events for critical parameter changes","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"This is a transparency issue only. It does not by itself cause realistic fund loss, lockup, insolvency, economic manipulation, or protocol-level DoS."},{"title":"High owner concentration - single point of failure","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Generic centralization risk without a distinct exploit path beyond the specific owner-controlled behavior already captured in F-004."}]}
